</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/kotaku/vip/~4/TbX7xioZO3o" height="1" width="1"/>";s:4:"link";s:69:"http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/kotaku/vip/~3/TbX7xioZO3o/soul-vaccination";s:4:"guid";s:14:"Kotaku-5892688";s:8:"category";s:20:"open threadOff Topic";s:7:"pubdate";s:29:"Mon, 12 Mar 2012 22:30:00 EDT";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:13:"Kirk Hamilton";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:85:"http://kotaku.com/index.php?op=postcommentfeed&postId=5892688&view=rss&microfeed=true";}s:10:"feedburner";a:1:{s:8:"origlink";s:42:"http://kotaku.com/5892688/soul-vaccination";}s:7:"summary";s:3285:"<p><img src="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/17g97hvcvhs9ujpg/medium.jpg" width="300" class="image_0 v10_medium" alt="Soul Vaccination"  title="Soul Vaccination" />Greetings <em>Kotaku</em>-eers, and welcome to a new week of evening open threads. I missed doing these last week during the Game Developers Conference! It's good to be back.</p>
