</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/kotaku/vip/~4/7dapEUScYSQ" height="1" width="1"/>";s:4:"link";s:53:"http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/kotaku/vip/~3/7dapEUScYSQ/";s:4:"guid";s:14:"Kotaku-5892651";s:8:"category";s:39:"ShoesArtFbNintendoSuper MariotweetZelda";s:7:"pubdate";s:29:"Mon, 12 Mar 2012 20:30:00 EDT";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:8:"Kate Cox";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:85:"http://kotaku.com/index.php?op=postcommentfeed&postId=5892651&view=rss&microfeed=true";}s:10:"feedburner";a:1:{s:8:"origlink";s:95:"http://kotaku.com/5892651/you-wont-jump-over-the-flagpole-in-these-awesome-mario-heels/gallery/";}s:7:"summary";s:3797:"<p><img src="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/17g8xuc1xor4ujpg/medium.jpg" width="300" class="image_0 v10_medium" alt="You Won't Jump Over the Flagpole in These Awesome Mario Heels"  title="You Won't Jump Over the Flagpole in These Awesome Mario Heels" /></p>
<p>Artist Jamie Ferraioli proves that stunning, feminine accessories are in no way at odds with nerd culture with her gorgeous, hand-painted shoes.</p>
<p>These heels and flats display meticulously detailed hand-painted art from <em>Super Mario Brothers</em> and <em>The Legend of Zelda</em>. My personal favorite part is the lava painted onto the platform sole of the black Mario heels.</p>
<p class="arrow"><a href="http://www.etsy.com/shop/magicbeanbuyer?section_id=10925870">Magicbeanbuyer's Shop</a> [Etsy, via <a href="http://www.buzzfeed.com/babymantis/hand-painted-nintendo-shoes-1opu">BuzzFeed</a>]</p>
