</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/kotaku/vip/~4/ihgOsgncFwY" height="1" width="1"/>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1331557200;}i:37;a:11:{s:5:"title";s:113:"&quot;Just For Kids&quot; Comes to PlayStation 3 Netflix, Still Waiting for &quot;Just for Adults&quot; [NetFlix]";s:11:"description";s:2599:"<p><a rel="lytebox" href="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/17g7i69n2h55wjpg/original.jpg"><img src="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/17g7i69n2h55wjpg/medium.jpg" width="300" class="image_0 v10_medium" alt="&quot;Just For Kids&quot; Comes to PlayStation 3 Netflix, Still Waiting for &quot;Just for Adults&quot;"  title="&quot;Just For Kids&quot; Comes to PlayStation 3 Netflix, Still Waiting for &quot;Just for Adults&quot;" /></a>The menacing black box lurking within your entertainment center just got a bit less menacing, as Netflix adds the bright and colorful "Just for Kids" to the PlayStation 3 version of its streaming video app.</p>
<p>For those of you unfamiliar, the picture above depicts the <em>Backyardigans</em>, a group of singing, dancing and imagineering young animals that always find things that they've never seen before in their backyard. That's why every day they're back for more.</p>
<p>These little bastards are a staple of Netflix's "Just for Kids" section. Already available on the PC and Wii and coming soon to the Xbox 360, tablets, and whatever else, "Just for Kids" give parents a way to graduate from having to strictly control their children's video intake to being able to go get a damn sandwich for crying out loud, damn kids.</p>
<p>I am familiar with this feeling. I am also familiar with the entire <em>Backyardigans</em> series. My nine-month-old children, on the other hand, only stay for the opening song and then go back to finding dangerous things to put in their mouths.</p>
<p>So yes, now your children have a destination for child-safe programming on the PC, perfect for winding down after a long day of <em>Modern Warfare 3</em>.</p>
<p>Now it's time for us to have a snack.</p><div class="feedflare">
